-- India Allows 2 Million Tons of Wheat Exports
-- B y   P r a t i k   P a r i j a
-- 2012-07-03T14:43:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/india-allows-2-million-tons-of-wheat-exports-correct-.html
(Corrects currency of export price.)  India  allowed the export of 2 million
metric tons of wheat from its own stocks, Food Minister K.V.
Thomas said in New Delhi today. The export, at a minimum price
of $228 a ton, will take place in tranches, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pratik Parija in New Delhi at 
 pparija@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
